d Benjamin as well as Bill Clinton’s impeachment and Nelson Mandela and Desmond Tutu’s testimonies before the Truth and Reconciliation Commission. The seminars conclude with an extended reading of Henri Thomas’s 1964 novel Le Parjure.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aForgiveness in literature. 0aForgivenessxPhilosophy. 0aForgivenessxPolitical aspects. 0aForgiveness-Political aspects. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aBennington, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrault, Pascale-Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChenoweth, Katie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCotton, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCotton, Nicholas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKamuf, Peggy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichaud, Ginette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichaud, Ginette, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNaas, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRottenberg, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTherezo, Rodrigo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTherezo, Rodrigo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWills, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226825298423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226825298/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b202